        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 4:30PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of Raton Crews Airport, or 16 miles west of Raton,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Maxwell and Raton Crews Airport.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 64 between Mile Markers 317 and 344...and
near Mile Marker 359.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 422 and 447.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
